article.headline: Toledo 77, West Georgia 62
article.story: MIAMI -- Ridley Johnson scored 17 points to help Toledo defeat Division II West Georgia 77-62 on Wednesday and post its first win of the season. The Rockets (1-4) outrebounded the Wolves 47-26 in the O'Reilly Auto Parts CBE Classic, giving first-year coach Gene Cross his first career victory. West Georgia (2-4), fresh off its 57-54 upset victory over host Florida International on Tuesday night, fell behind early. Toledo led 40-30 at halftime and by as many as 18 points in the second half. Anthony Byrd added 13 points for the Rockets, while Jonathan Amos, Tyrone Kent and Justin Anyijong scored 10 points apiece. The Rockets turned the ball over only 14 times after committing 25 turnovers in each of their previous two games. Doug Daniels led West Georgia with 14 points, while Ish John scored 11 and Chris Colvin added 10.
